"{\n  \"text\": \"So fermented foods are not only great for building gut health when we've diminished it, but they're great for getting the nutrients and vitamins out of our food, even when we do have a healthy gut. But this isn't the only benefit of fermented foods. Fermented foods for someone who has a perfectly healthy gut are a wonderful food as well because fermented foods are basically a pre-digestion of our food. We uh when when we create an anaerobic environment and let anaerobic bacteria circulate and feed off of our foods, we're basically breaking them down in the same way our guts will do with anaerobic bacteria. So when we give it two-week or a week long or however long you're fermenting your foods, uh head start with that bacteria, a lot of the compounds within those vegetables that carry our nutrients and our vitamins and our minerals are broken down in such ways that they make it much more digestible to us. So these um these compounds that a lot of times are passed through us because they're still bound up in a way that we can't digest them, are digested much more readily when we allow the bacteria to do their work breaking down these compounds beforehand.\",\n  \"sentences\": [\n    {\n      \"text\": \" So fermented foods are not only great for building gut health when we've diminished it, but they're great for getting the nutrients and vitamins out of our food, even when we do have a healthy gut.\",\n      \"start\": 0.08,\n      \"end\": 11.28,\n      \"duration\": 11.2,\n      \"confidence\": 0.995,\n      \"tokens\": [\n        {\n          \"text\": \" So\",\n          \"start\": 0.08,\n          \"end\": 0.32,\n          \"duration\": 0.24,\n          \"confidence\": 0.997\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \" fer\",\n          \"start\": 0.4,\n          \"end\": 0.64,\n          \"duration\": 0.24,\n          \"confidence\": 1.0\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"mente\",\n          \"start\": 0.64,\n          \"end\": 0.8